"Today it is recognized that 99.999% of all observable matter in the universe is in the plasma state and plasmas are found at temperatures and densities far exceeding those that will support matter in the first three states"

(Plasma Physics at https://books.google.com/books?vid=ISBN079235527X&id=ZSlJRAeL95sC&pg=PA57&lpg=PA57&ots=jnEIJGfx6t#v=onepage&q&f=false)
alfredsnippet.name: Phys.org Post - Plasma is 99% of Observable Matter - part 02
